HEADWORD: Saltirewise
<hw>Sal"tire*wise`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <fld>(Her.)</fld>
<def>In the manner of a saltire; -- said especially of the blazoning of
a shield divided by two lines drawn in the direction of a bend and a
bend sinister, and crossing at the center.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saltish</ent>⟦br⟧
